<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="346" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,327,677]" pageId="11" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,436,461]" pageId="11" pageNumber="346">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[325,569,436,461]" class="Arachnida" family="Axonopsidae" genus="Brachypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubidata">
<emphasis box="[325,569,436,461]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="346">Brachypoda rubidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described in the both sexes from a pond in Bosung (
<bibRefCitation author="Kim" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" refString="Kim, I-H. &amp; Chung, K-S. (1996) Water Mites of Axonopsinae (Acarina, Aturidae) from Korea. The Korean Journal of Systematic Zoology, 12, 137 - 165." type="journal article" year="1996">
Kim and Chung 
<number box="[151,211,471,496]" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kim &amp; Chung, 1996" authorityName="Kim &amp; Chung" authorityYear="1996" box="[396,741,471,496]" class="Arachnida" family="Axonopsidae" genus="Brachypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rapida">
<emphasis box="[396,502,471,496]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="346">B. rapida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kim" box="[509,741,471,496]" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" refString="Kim, I-H. &amp; Chung, K-S. (1996) Water Mites of Axonopsinae (Acarina, Aturidae) from Korea. The Korean Journal of Systematic Zoology, 12, 137 - 165." type="journal article" year="1996">
Kim &amp; Chung, 
<number box="[685,741,471,496]" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[756,903,471,496]" name="South Korea" pageId="11" pageNumber="346">South Korea</collectingCountry>
), but can be easily distinguished from the latter in the both sexes by the presence of two red posterolateral patches (
<figureCitation box="[915,1049,508,533]" captionStart="FIGURE 9 A – E. A – B" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1856,1878]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,772,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,772,1835]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9 A – E. A – B Photographs of Brachypoda rubidata Kim &amp; Chung, 1996, male: A = idiosoma, ventral view; B = idiosoma, dorsal view. C – E Photographs of sampling sites: C = CR 9 (stream in Naebyeansan NP, South Korea, locus typicus of Brachypoda milicaae sp. n.; D = CR 10 (pool near stream in Naebyeansan NP, South Korea, sampling site of Brachypoda rubidata Kim &amp; Chung, 1996); E = Levaya Burinda River, Russia, locus typicus of Brachypoda sokolowi sp. n. and B. rossica sp. n. Photos. V. Pešić (Figs. A – D), K. Semenchenko (Fig. E)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231441/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="346">
Figs. 
<number box="[979,993,508,532]" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" value="9.0">9</number>
A–B
</figureCitation>
), dorsal and ventral shield stouter, posteriorly not narrowed as in 
<taxonomicName box="[494,600,543,568]" class="Arachnida" family="Axonopsidae" genus="Brachypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rapida">
<emphasis box="[494,600,543,568]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="346">B. rapida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and by the differently shaped genital field (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Kim" box="[1140,1386,543,568]" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" refString="Kim, I-H. &amp; Chung, K-S. (1996) Water Mites of Axonopsinae (Acarina, Aturidae) from Korea. The Korean Journal of Systematic Zoology, 12, 137 - 165." type="journal article" year="1996">
Kim and Chung 
<number box="[1326,1386,543,568]" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,327,677]" pageId="11" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,580,605]" pageId="11" pageNumber="346">Habitat.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kim" box="[306,569,580,605]" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" refString="Kim, I-H. &amp; Chung, K-S. (1996) Water Mites of Axonopsinae (Acarina, Aturidae) from Korea. The Korean Journal of Systematic Zoology, 12, 137 - 165." type="journal article" year="1996">
Kim and Chung (
<number box="[503,561,580,605]" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" value="1996.0">1996</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
stated that they found this species in a lake. We found this species in a pool near stream (
<figureCitation box="[296,383,615,640]" captionStart="FIGURE 9 A – E. A – B" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1856,1878]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,772,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,772,1835]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9 A – E. A – B Photographs of Brachypoda rubidata Kim &amp; Chung, 1996, male: A = idiosoma, ventral view; B = idiosoma, dorsal view. C – E Photographs of sampling sites: C = CR 9 (stream in Naebyeansan NP, South Korea, locus typicus of Brachypoda milicaae sp. n.; D = CR 10 (pool near stream in Naebyeansan NP, South Korea, sampling site of Brachypoda rubidata Kim &amp; Chung, 1996); E = Levaya Burinda River, Russia, locus typicus of Brachypoda sokolowi sp. n. and B. rossica sp. n. Photos. V. Pešić (Figs. A – D), K. Semenchenko (Fig. E)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231441/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="346">
Fig. 
<number box="[348,362,616,640]" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" value="9.0">9</number>
D
</figureCitation>
) with typical lenitobiontic species of the genera 
<taxonomicName box="[928,1152,615,640]" class="Arachnida" family="Arrenuridae" genus="Thoracophoracarus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[928,1152,615,640]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="346">Thoracophoracarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1207,1322,617,640]" class="Arachnida" family="Unionicolidae" genus="Neumania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1207,1322,617,640]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="346">Neumania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
